Story Time with FX Utilising the cutecharts library, created visuals from Children Story books dataset from Kaggle. Also performed Machine Learning with sklearn Random Forrest Classifier and Naive Bayes to predict the Stage those stories are for. Power BI - USA Obesity Rate Recreated 1st Group Project which was completed with Python's pandas and matplotlib. This version's visualisation was realised by Microsoft's Power BI. The dataset was revisited and further explored. Tableau - CitiBike Used Tableau to visualize 6 months of CitiBike usage data. Explored station's popularity, peak usage, maintenance requirements, and investigated on user's age. ETL - Financing Used Cars Extract, Load and Transformed Data from a local car dealership and finder.com.au. To Analyse between comparison loans provided by car dealer and financial institution. Leaflet-Earthquake Analysis Read Earthquake data from UGSS in GeoJson format using D3 and added layers onto the map using Leaflet. Project Utilising Plotly to create interactive charts after reading json data with D3. The charts would change according to which Subject ID is chosen. D3 manipulating Data Visualization - Data Journalism Utilising D3, users are able to interact with the scatter plot by selecting the X and Y Axis Labels and the Scatter plot would change dynamically after fetching the appropriate data. Project Group project on New York State's State Park Attendance. Used Leaflet, D3, Plotly and ChartJS for the charts visualisation. The site is deployed on Heroku. Go to the site Project Collaboration with Helen for the final project. Used splinter to scrape data, pandas to clean and Tableau to visualised the data. Further filtered and prepared the data for Machine Learning. We used the Lasso Linear Regression model as it has the most ideal accuracy. The site is then deployed on Heroku.
